parameters.anneal_offsets: A list of anneal offsets for each working qubit (NaN if unused).
parameters.anneal_schedule: A piecewise linear annealing schedule specified by a list of points.
parameters.annealing_time: A positive integer that sets the duration (in microseconds) of quantum annealing time.
parameters.flux_biases: A list of flux biases for each working qubit.
parameters.flux_drift_compensation: A boolean for whether to activate the flux drift compensation.
parameters.h_gain_schedule: A piecewise linear h-gain schedule specified by a list of points.
parameters.initial_state: The initial states to use for the reverse anneal feature.
parameters.programming_thermalization: An integer that gives the time (in microseconds) to wait after programming the processor in order for it to cool back to base temperature..
parameters.readout_thermalization: An integer that gives the time (in microseconds) to wait after each state is read from the processor in order for it to cool back to base temperature.
parameters.reduce_intersample_correlation: A boolean for whether to add pauses between samples.
parameters.reinitialize_state: Whether to reapply the initial_state for every read.
